<br>
1). An explosion in a vacuum (so there is no shockwave)<br>
<br>
2). A highly reflective parabolic surface on the inside with an opening at the other end of the structure to reflect the intense EM radiation outside of the ship<br>
<br>
3). Make sure the reflective material is multi-layered and can be used as ablative material (in order to vaporize and carry away excess heat) <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#6F6F6F>- </font><a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace>NuclearSpace Message Board</a><font color=#6F6F6F> - </font><a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4>Nuclear Power in Space</a> <font color=#6F6F6F> - </font><a href="http://www.nuclearspace.com">NuclearSpace Home Page</a><font color=#6F6F6F> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.246c<br>Copyright ©1999-2003 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

